UMLDescription: The user class is a representation of an application user.
ConceptDefinition: An individual who uses a computer, program, network, or related service for work or entertainment. (from http://www.computeruser.com/resources/dictionary/index.html)

UMLDescription: This a unique id to identify a user within an application.
ConceptDefinition: An individual who uses a computer, program, network, or related service for work or entertainment. (from http://www.computeruser.com/resources/dictionary/index.html)

UMLDescription: This string is used for login into the application.
ConceptDefinition: A login name is the account name used to access a computer system. Also called user ID or user name, it is a way people identify themselves to their online service or Internet access provider. (learntheweb.com)

UMLDescription: The first name of the user
ConceptDefinition: A word or group of words indicating a person's first (personal) name. (NCI)

UMLDescription: The last name of the user
ConceptDefinition: A word or group of words indicating a person's last (family) name. (NCI)

UMLDescription: The name of the organization that this user belongs to.
ConceptDefinition: Organizational unit like a laboratory, institute or consortium. (caBIO)

UMLDescription: The name of the department that this user belongs to.
ConceptDefinition: The name of the department that this user belongs to.

UMLDescription: The name of the title for this user.
ConceptDefinition: An identifying appellation signifying status or function.

UMLDescription: This is the work phone of the user.
ConceptDefinition: A telephone number is a sequence of decimal digits (0-9) that is used for identifying a destination telephone line or other device in a telephone network.  In the US this is a ten digit number resembling "123-456-7890".

UMLDescription: The password used to login into the application
ConceptDefinition: A secret set of characters, numbers, or symbols used as a form of authentication.

UMLDescription: Email id for this user.
ConceptDefinition: An e-mail address identifies a location to which e-mail can be delivered. A modern Internet e-mail address (using SMTP) is a string of the form jsmith@domain.example. (from Wikipedia)

UMLDescription: It is the start date for this user.
ConceptDefinition: The calendar date on which something is to start or did start.

UMLDescription: It is the end date for this user.
ConceptDefinition: The calendar date on which an activity is terminated or completed. (NCI)

UMLDescription: It is the date when the user information was last updated
ConceptDefinition: The particular day, month and year an event will happen or has happened.

UMLDescription: It is the date when the user information was last updated
ConceptDefinition: Bring up to date; supply with recent information or technology.
